<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
The Mongolian population of 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1809" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1787" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Euchroeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euchroeus purpuratus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="purpuratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Euchroeus purpuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly separated from the western form by different punctation of clypeus, with small punctures and polished interspaces without micropunctation (vs. denser punctures, micropunctate on interspaces); elongate, spiniform process on propleuron and antero-ventrally on mesopleuron; metasoma mostly without darker bands. Future barcoding analysis will clarify the affinities between the western and Mongolian populations. Interestingly, another Mongolian species close to the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1809" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Euchroeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Euchroeus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Euchroeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, namely 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rosa &amp; Halada" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Spinolia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Spinolia spinosa" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Spinolia spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rosa &amp; Halada in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.999.58536" author="Rosa, P" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" pagination="49 - 107" refId="B28" refString="Rosa, P, Proshchalykin, MYu, Halada, M, Aibek, U, 2020. First checklist of the chrysidid wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) of Mongolia, with description of new species. ZooKeys 999: 49 - 107, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.999.58536" title="First checklist of the chrysidid wasps (Hymenoptera, Chrysididae) of Mongolia, with description of new species." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.999.58536" volume="999" year="2020">Rosa et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
, shares similar spines on propleuron.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
